<subSubSection id="0F36C1D5F0D76442C53664D68EB5E3C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D8CEC1D33F9105B5186A8C82A1C8656C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="E5DED9E23BE05B77B848D6B8DFBD4193" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B20F2D9234E2C6A44651BFC1A077B468" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Head globose, body cylindrical. Male tegmina well developed. Male subgenital plate concave or deeply notched; dorsal lobes of ectoparameres externally visible; styli present on the posterolateral corners of epiphallus. Female tegmina reduced to small pads; ovipositor straight, slender, needle-shaped.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
